South African Gold Production Fell by 1.6% in Fourth Quarter, Chamber Says

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-03-14T12:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/south-african-gold-production-fell-by-1-6-in-fourth-quarter-chamber-says.html
South African gold production fell
1.6 percent to 1.597 million ounces during the fourth quarter
compared with the previous three months, the Chamber of Mines of  South Africa  said.  Compared with the fourth quarter of 2009, gold output fell
3.9 percent during the three months to Dec. 31, the chamber said
in an e-mailed statement today.  Gold production during 2010 fell 6.4 percent from a year
earlier, said the chamber, which represents producers including  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) ,  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  and Harmony Gold Mining
Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at   ajordan11@bloomberg.net  